POLRDataEntry.pokedex: With nerves of steel, nothing can perturb it. It is more agile and active than it appears.

POLRDataEntry.name: Bibarel
POLRDataEntry.pokedex: It makes its nest by damming streams with bark and mud. It is known as an industrious worker.

POLRDataEntry.name: Kricketot
POLRDataEntry.pokedex: It shakes its head back to front, causing its antennae to hit each other and sound like a xylophone.

POLRDataEntry.name: Kricketune
POLRDataEntry.pokedex: It crosses its knifelike arms in front of its chest when it cries. It can compose melodies ad lib.

POLRDataEntry.name: Shinx
POLRDataEntry.pokedex: All of its fur dazzles if danger is sensed. It flees while the foe is momentarily blinded.

POLRDataEntry.name: Luxio
POLRDataEntry.pokedex: Its claws loose electricity with enough amperage to cause fainting. They live in small groups.

POLRDataEntry.name: Luxray
POLRDataEntry.pokedex: It has eyes that can see through anything. It spots and captures prey hiding behind objects.

POLRDataEntry.name: Budew
POLRDataEntry.pokedex: Over the winter, it closes its bud and endures the cold. In spring, the bud opens and releases pollen.

POLRDataEntry.name: Roserade
POLRDataEntry.pokedex: It attracts prey with a sweet aroma, then downs it with thorny whips hidden in its arms.

POLRDataEntry.name: Cranidos
POLRDataEntry.pokedex: It lived in jungles around 100 million years ago. Its skull is as hard as iron.

POLRDataEntry.name: Rampardos
POLRDataEntry.pokedex: Its powerful head butt has enough power to shatter even the most durable things upon impact.

POLRDataEntry.name: Shieldon
POLRDataEntry.pokedex: A Pok�mon that lived in jungles around 100 million years ago. Its facial hide is extremely hard.

POLRDataEntry.name: Bastiodon
POLRDataEntry.pokedex: Any frontal attack is repulsed. It is a docile Pok�mon that feeds on grass and berries.

POLRDataEntry.name: Burmy
POLRDataEntry.pokedex: To shelter itself from cold, wintry winds, it covers itself with a cloak made of twigs and leaves.

POLRDataEntry.name: Wormadam
POLRDataEntry.pokedex: When BURMY evolved, its cloak became a part of this Pok�mon�s body. The cloak is never shed.

POLRDataEntry.name: Wormadam-g
POLRDataEntry.pokedex: When BURMY evolved, its cloak became a part of this Pok�mon�s body. The cloak is never shed.

POLRDataEntry.name: Wormadam-s
POLRDataEntry.pokedex: When BURMY evolved, its cloak became a part of this Pok�mon�s body. The cloak is never shed.

POLRDataEntry.name: Mothim
POLRDataEntry.pokedex: It loves the honey of flowers and steals honey collected by COMBEE.

POLRDataEntry.name: Combee
POLRDataEntry.pokedex: A Pok�mon formed by three others. It busily carries sweet floral honey to VESPIQUEN.

POLRDataEntry.name: Vespiquen
POLRDataEntry.pokedex: Its abdomen is a honeycomb for grubs. It raises its grubs on honey collected by COMBEE.

POLRDataEntry.name: Pachirisu
POLRDataEntry.pokedex: It makes fur balls that crackle with static electricity. It stores them with berries in tree holes.

POLRDataEntry.name: Buizel
POLRDataEntry.pokedex: It has a flotation sac that is like an inflatable collar. It floats on water with its head out.

POLRDataEntry.name: Floatzel
POLRDataEntry.pokedex: It floats using its well-developed flotation sac. It assists in the rescues of drowning people.

POLRDataEntry.name: Cherubi
POLRDataEntry.pokedex: The small ball holds the nutrients needed for evolution. Apparently, it is very sweet and tasty.

POLRDataEntry.name: Cherrim
POLRDataEntry.pokedex: It blooms during times of strong sunlight. It tries to make up for everything it endured as a bud.

POLRDataEntry.name: Shellos
POLRDataEntry.pokedex: Its colors and shapes differ from region to region. In the Sinnoh region, two types are confirmed.

POLRDataEntry.name: Gastrodon
POLRDataEntry.pokedex: It has a pliable body without any bones. If any part of its body is torn off, it grows right back.

POLRDataEntry.name: Ambipom
POLRDataEntry.pokedex: To eat, it deftly shucks nuts with its two tails. It rarely uses its arms now.

POLRDataEntry.name: Drifloon
POLRDataEntry.pokedex: A Pok�mon formed by the spirits of people and Pok�mon. It loves damp, humid seasons.

POLRDataEntry.name: Drifblim
POLRDataEntry.pokedex: It�s drowzy in daytime, but flies off in the evening in big groups. No one knows where they go.

POLRDataEntry.name: Buneary
POLRDataEntry.pokedex: It slams foes by sharply uncoiling its rolled ears. It stings enough to make a grown-up cry in pain.

POLRDataEntry.name: Lopunny
POLRDataEntry.pokedex: An extremely cautious Pok�mon. It cloaks its body with its fluffy ear fur when it senses danger.

POLRDataEntry.name: Mismagius
POLRDataEntry.pokedex: Its cries sound like incantations. Those hearing it are tormented by headaches and hallucinations.

POLRDataEntry.name: Honchkrow
POLRDataEntry.pokedex: Becoming active at night, it is known to swarm with numerous MURKROW in tow.

POLRDataEntry.name: Glameow
POLRDataEntry.pokedex: It claws if displeased and purrs when affectionate. Its fickleness is very popular among some.

POLRDataEntry.name: Purugly
POLRDataEntry.pokedex: It is a brazen brute that barges its way into another Pok�mon�s nest and claims it as its own.

POLRDataEntry.name: Chingling
POLRDataEntry.pokedex: It emits cries by agitating an orb at the back of its throat. It moves with flouncing hops.

POLRDataEntry.name: Stunky
